headline: General Partner at Spark Capital
investment_locations: San Francisco, California, Oakland, California, Los Angeles, California, Toronto, Ontario, New York, New York
areas_of_interest_freeform: Primarily a consumer and marketplace investor, Nabeel seeks out entrepreneurs who develop that rare combination of design and technology to transform markets. He looks for products in which the underlying technology can be complex, but are presented as a simple, magical experience to the people who use them. This is more about characteristics of the company & founders than markets, so I spend time in everything from robotics to social media to hospitality to on demand economy.
no_current_interest_freeform: Not interested in non-product experiences, so deep enterprise software where the end consumer is not the buyer is likely not a fit.

headline: I founded and manage Champion Hill, a pre-seed/seed firm.  We also make 1-2 later stage SPV investments/year.
investment_locations: Atlanta, Georgia, Austin, Texas, San Francisco Bay Area, London, Singapore, Los Angeles, California, Raleigh-Durham / Southeast US
areas_of_interest_freeform:
We are one of the few firms that will invest in defense, and yes we will invest in weapons if it makes sense to do so.  Past investments are SpaceX (2014), Anduril (2017), Umbra (2018), Modern Intelligence (2021)

We are also keenly interested in digital sovereignty:  Eco.com, Skiff.com, Keys.casa, and the Urbit ecosystem (Uqbar, Tirrel, Zorp etc). 

We have a bucket for curveballs: things that don't fit in buckets.  Flexport (2015), Brella (2019) Fount.bio (2019) Coop.farm (2022).
no_current_interest_freeform: We feel that the world doesn't need the n+1 investor in enterprise SaaS, mainstream fintech, or ecommerce.  We are most interested in things for which nobody knows who the best investors in the world are.

headline: General Partner at TNT Ventures
investment_locations: San Francisco Bay Area, San Francisco, California
areas_of_interest_freeform: Broadly, I am interested in any business that have great teams working in very large markets. Typically I like to see them when they have a small number of users/customers that love the product (pre-seed/seed) and I prefer to commit to rounds early and help founders put together the rest of the round whether it's pre-seed or Series A.
no_current_interest_freeform:
I am not interested in areas I don't understand: ad tech, security, biotech. I don't like anything "for millennials."

I am not interested in late-stage rounds. 

I am willing to look at a deck/blurb for just about anything though and am always curious to learn.

headline: General Partner, Co-Founder at Agent Capital
investment_locations: Boston, Massachusetts, San Francisco Bay Area, Chicago, Illinois
areas_of_interest_freeform:
We are in the midst of a golden era for biotechnology & pharmaceuticals brought on by recent breakthroughs in genomics, proteomics & new treatment modalities (e.g., gene & cell therapy).

I am interested in finding passionate founders and entrepreneurs utilizing these new foundational tools to unlock novel treatments to extend human life for conditions with the highest unmet medical need (e.g., cancer, aging, rare diseases, neurodegeneration, etc.).
no_current_interest_freeform: I am less interested in therapies that offer incremental improvements (otherwise known as "me too" or fast follower therapies), or those therapies being developed for conditions that are well cared for with existing medicines.
